OL,3,CTraineeship wages reinstated in
OL,4,Cgovernment u-turn
OL,6,FThe Department for Employment, Social
OL,7,FSecurity & Housing say the u-turn was
OL,8,Fmotivated by a recognition that lower
OL,9,Ftrainee wages allow for greater access
OL,10,Fto skilled employment for islanders at
OL,11,Fthe start of their careers.
OL,13,FThe Minister for Social Security,
OL,14,FDeputy Lyndsay Feltham, says she
OL,15,Funderstands the wages "create more
OL,16,Fopportunities and help make the
OL,17,Ftransition into skilled jobs clearer
OL,18,Fand more accessible" and "support
OL,19,Fbusinesses to invest in trainees as
OL,20,Fpart of building a strong, inclusive
OL,21,Feconomy".
